# Rebuild and Launch After App Changes

When a turn modifies ClipStack app code or project files (Swift sources, entitlements, Xcode project, etc.), finish the turn by quitting, rebuilding, and launching the app.

## When to run

Run this workflow when the turn changes anything that affects the running app binary, including:
- Swift source under `ClipStack/`
- `ClipStack.xcodeproj/`
- Entitlements, Info.plist, or other app bundle config

Skip when the turn is read-only (questions, reviews, docs-only) or touches only non-app files (e.g. README).

## Commands

Run from the repo root:

```bash
pkill -x ClipStack 2>/dev/null || true
sleep 0.5
cd /Users/theorichardson/Projects/ClipStack
xcodebuild -scheme ClipStack -destination 'platform=macOS' build
open "$(xcodebuild -scheme ClipStack -destination 'platform=macOS' -showBuildSettings 2>/dev/null | awk -F' = ' '/^    BUILT_PRODUCTS_DIR / {print $2; exit}')/ClipStack.app"
```

If the build fails, report the failure and do not launch.

Briefly confirm in the response that ClipStack was quit, rebuilt, and relaunched.
